data.text:
Porsche (AG) is a German sport car company that manufactures very expensive cars, with the basic models costing usually over $100,000. Porsche specializes in making high-performance sport cars, which explains in the cost of the cars made.

History[]

Dr. Ing. h.c. F. Porsche AG, or just shortened to Porsche AG, was founded in Austria in 1931 by a man named Ferdinand Porsche. Porsche AG then moved to its main offices at Kronenstra√üe 24 in the center of Stuttgart. While the company was new, the German government gave them an assignment to design a car for the citizens of Germany, that is, a "Volkswagen". This lead to the design of the Volkswagen Beetle.
